.TH daft-install 1  "daft-install 1.14.5" 
.SH NAME
daft\-install \- Install a starter daft.yml in the current worktree
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdaft\-install\fR [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Creates a starter daft.yml at the current worktree root with a commented
skeleton covering the major sections (hooks, shared, layout). Modeled on
`lefthook install`.
.PP
If daft.yml already exists, the command refuses without modifying anything;
edit the existing file with your editor or a future `daft config` TUI.
.PP
No git side effects: daft does not write to .gitignore or .git/info/exclude.
Ignore rules are the user\*(Aqs responsibility.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress progress reporting
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v1.14.5
